-----BEGIN PLACEHOLDER — REPLACE THIS FILE-----
This is not a real key. License verification will fail until you replace
this file's contents.

Steps:
  1. Run `python3 -m licensing.keygen` once, on your own machine.
  2. Open ~/.sam_signing_keys/sam_public_key.pem
  3. Copy its ENTIRE contents (including the real -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
     and -----END PUBLIC KEY----- lines) and paste them here, replacing
     this whole file.
  4. Commit the updated licensing/public_key.pem to git — it's safe to
     commit, it's public by design. Never commit the private key.
-----END PLACEHOLDER-----
